sentence: Wednesday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index up above 8000 points.
The index first reached the 8000 mark on Aug 27, 2018.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 3.05 billion.
Advancers stocks led declining by 1.61 to 1 ratio.
There were 1927 advancers and 1195 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 27 stocks reached a 52 week high and 63 those reaching lows totaled.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed up .12% for the day; a total of 9.15 points.
Microchip Technology Incorporated ( MCHP ) had the largest percent change down (-3.26%) while Wynn Resorts, Limited ( WYNN ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.69%.
The Dow Jones index closed up .2% for the day; a total of 54.45 points.
Procter & Gamble Company (The) ( PG ) had the largest percent change down (-1.58%) while Caterpillar, Inc. ( CAT ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.2%.
